==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*bugan-''.  Cognate with Old Frisian ''boga'', Old Saxon [[bogo]] (Dutch [[boog]]), Old High German [[bogo]] (German [[Bogen]]), Old Norse [[bogi]] (Swedish [[båge]]).

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'boɣa/

===Noun===
'''boga''' ''m''
# something bent or curved, especially a [[bow]]
#:''hie leton garas fleogan, bogan wæron bysige'': they let arrows fly, bows were busy.  (''Battle of Maldon'')

